📍Grotta Palazzese is a famous restaurant located in Polignano a Mare, a picturesque coastal town in the Puglia region of Italy. What makes Grotta Palazzese unique is its stunning and unusual setting inside a natural limestone cave that overlooks the Adriatic Sea. The restaurant is situated within a cave that has been eroded by the sea over centuries, creating a remarkable dining experience in Italy.

Capri beach clubs are iconic, but there are so many options! 

Here are my top 4 choices: 

🩵Da Luigi ai Faraglioni - this is probably my least favorite of my top 4, however, it is still a great way to spend your day. It has great sun exposure and a nice swimming spot. Expect to spend about €125 per person for a lounge chair and lunch. 

🧡Bagni Internazionale - this beach club has the most affordable prices and has an actual pebble beach as opposed to the other clubs that have a ladder into the water. This is a great club to go to if you are traveling as a family as the kids can swim in the shallow waters. I spent about €75 for my chair, a couple drinks and a delicious panino. 

💙La Fontelina - the most iconic of Capri’s beach clubs known for their blue and white striped aesthetic. This club is a splurge, but you get what you pay for. Every dish I have tasted here has been phenomenal and the drinks are excellent. Service is great, but it’s very difficult to get a reservation during high season so planning ahead is an absolute must. Expect to spend about €180 per person for the day.

🩶Lido Del Faro - without a doubt, this is my favorite beach club on the island. Located on the southwest tip, it offers crystal clear waters and the best service you can imagine. This club also has a pool if you prefer to take a dip there instead of the sea. Because it’s located away from the main areas of the island, Lido Del Faro offers a more local and laid back experience with all the same luxuries as the other clubs. I spend about €125 for a daybed and lunch (spaghetti vongole). Make sure to stay in the area and catch what will most likely be the most beautiful sunset of your life. 

Save this for your 2024 Italian Holiday 🫶🏼

Matera, Italy, a city with a history spanning over 9,000 years, is renowned for its ancient charm. In 2019, this town was designated as the European capital of culture and I completely understood why as I walked through the stone streets. #travelitaly #luxurytravel #ladolcevita

Mornings in Positano are synonymous with leisurely walks along charming, winding streets, sipping espresso at local cafes, and gazing out at the sparkling Tyrrhenian Sea. The scent of fresh Italian pastries mingles with the salty sea breeze, inviting you to savor the town’s culinary delights. Whether you choose to relax on the pebbly shores of Spiaggia Grande, shop for artisanal treasures, or simply soak in the breathtaking views, Positano’s mornings offer a tranquil and enchanting start to your day on the Amalfi Coast. #travelitaly #amalficoast #traveltoitaly

Travel Tuesday is coming up on November 28th with some amazing deals! So it’s time to start thinking about your 2024 travels. What destinations are on your bucket list for next year? Link in bio to work with me 🫶🏼

HERE 👇🏼
•
•
•
1. Boat Day along the coast of San Vito, Polignano a Mare and Monopoli. Swim in some of the most incredible grottos and bright blue waters while you enjoy local snacks and wines. Simply put, boat days are the best days. 

2. Day trip to Alberobello and/or Matera. Both of these towns are within a couple of hours from Polignano a Mare. Alberobello is charming and unique whereas Matera is ancient and traditional. Both towns offer local cuisines and incredible views.

3. Get a Caffè Speciale at Il Super Mago Del Gelo. I wish I was kidding when I say that I get at least two a day when I am there. Made with a lemon peel, homemade cream and amaretto, this drink is one of my favorite things I have discovered in Italy. 

4. Beach day at Lama Monachile. This famous beach has been photographed for years. We have so much fun here living like a local. Make sure to pack a lunch, some water shoes and arrive early enough to get a flat spot. This is a rocky beach! 

5. Dinner at Ristorante Grotta Palazzese. I did an entire post on this restaurant because it’s purely iconic. Their tasting menus are incredibly crafted to give you a culinary experience while dining inside an actual grotto as the waves crash under you. This is an expensive spot to dine at, but for a good reason. Luckily most of the other restaurants in the area are relatively cheap so you can save some cash on other meals.

I wish I was posting these with a different caption. I wish more than anything that I was announcing that we were finally having our first baby but God has a different plan for us. What was probably the best day of my life is now tainted with grief. Knowing that miscarriages are common doesn’t take the pain away however, it keeps us hopeful that we will get our rainbow baby someday. I hesitated to share this to the world but this loss has softened me in a way that has change my heart forever. Instagram is a generally a highlight reel however I can’t go on posting about my trips and daily life as if this hasn’t shaken me to the core. Leaning on women that have endured this kind of darkness has helped me immensely so I’m hoping that I can be that light for someone in the future. This has all taught me that life is so precious and how far small acts of kindness can go even when you don’t know someone is hurting. Thank you for all the love, support and prayers that have kept us going this past week ❤️‍🩹

Why you should stay the night on Capri and skip the day trip! 👇🏼
•
The crowds. The day trip crowds flood the city during the daylight hours and you are herded through the small streets. The city center becomes extremely touristy with group tours, full buses and long taxi lines. The shops and restaurants get quite overwhelmed and you will only get to go or see a couple places due to the crowds. 
•
Staying on the island allows you to explore the city centers in the evenings at a much more leisurely pace. It also allows you to spend time on the outskirts of the island, which are the best spots in my opinion. 
•
THE SUNSETS. I don’t have to explain myself here, just look at my Capri highlights. Other cities like Positano are facing South, so you won’t get a sunset like Capri does (specifically Anacapri)
•
You also get to converse with the locals more. I have met some of my favorite people that I now get to call friends on this island. 
•
The hotels here are so unique and offer an entirely different experience than other hotels in the Amalfi Coast area. The passion and pride than Caprese natives hold for this island shows through the way they treat visitors. See my Capri Q&A highlight for my favorite hotels (I can get you perks at these!)
•
Hope this helps anyone planning a trip to the Amalfi Coast, link is in my bio to work with me 🇮🇹❣️

Prost! Everyone should experience a true German beer festival at least once in their lifetime. 
🍻
OKTOBERFEST TIPS: 
•
1. Plan ahead! Oktoberfest in Germany may seem like a year away, but the planning should start in the next few months if you’re serious about going and doing it right. Table reservations are necessary and difficult to get with the language barrier. Allowing yourself enough time to purchase them is important especially if you do not want to pay a premium price. 

2. Location! A lot of people have asked where you should stay in Munich for the festival. In my experience, the transportation system in the city is extremely reliable, and you can stay anywhere within 20 to 30 minutes of the festival grounds and still have a wonderful experience getting to and from. One time I stayed within walking distance and another I stayed a short cab right away. Both were great! 

3. Outfits! For women, a traditional dirndl is appropriate. There are several shops in the city that sell them at an affordable price if you allow yourself enough time to shop before your festival day. There are also online shops that shipped to the US! I would personally avoid getting one on Amazon as they tend to look cheap and take away business from the authentic sellers in Germany. For men, a lederhosen is perfect. We got Ryan’s on Amazon and it was great quality. Also, I’m a huge advocate for comfortable shoes. A lot of women do wear booties or heels but I can imagine they weren’t able to dance around as easily. 

4. Time! There are a few “shifts” in the beer tents that last about 4 to 5 hours. The morning/midday shifts are a bit less wild, and the party starts for the dinner and later shifts. I would recommend an evening time slot at Paulner, Hacker, Hofbräu or Augustiner. 

5. Cost! Entry to the festival is free. You will need to purchase tickets for rides and reservations at the beer tents. This also goes for the festival food. Tickets and table reservations at the beer tents can range from $80-$1000 depending on your location, date and time of day.
